      <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersG8"/>
      <p><a href="ch66s02.html#MonstersG8">Genies</a> are humanlike beings who dwell on the <a href="ch65s02.html#MonstersE-F7">elemental</a> planes. They are famous for their strength, guile, and skill with illusion magic.</p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id1781126"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersG9"/>
        <p><a href="ch66s02.html#MonstersG8">Genies</a> prefer to outmaneuver and outthink their foes. They are not too proud to flee if it means they'll live to fight another day. If trapped, they bargain, offering treasure or favors in return for their lives and freedom.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1781155"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersG10"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong><span class="emphasis"><em>Plane Shift</em></span> (Sp):</strong></span> A <a href="ch66s02.html#MonstersG8">genie</a> can enter any of the <a href="ch65s02.html#MonstersE-F7">elemental</a> planes, the Astral Plane, or the Material Plane. This ability transports the <a href="ch66s02.html#MonstersG8">genie</a> and up to eight other creatures, provided they all link hands with the <a href="ch66s02.html#MonstersG8">genie</a>. It is otherwise similar to the spell of the same name (caster level 13th).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
